A 37-YEAR-OLD sergeant from Limpopo was arrested on Tuesday, 31 May by the Hawks for alleged corruption. According to Captain Matimba Maluleke, it’ alleged that in December 2017 the cop was on duty with his colleague, aged 42. Maluleke said the duo was patrolling in the Sekhukhune policing area when they saw a suspicious tractor and pulled it over. READ: Uzalo actress: 'I’m not a cop in real life'! “The driver of the tractor was searched and the police allegedly found dagga in his pocket. The duo reportedly demanded gratification from the driver. It is reported that a total of R2 100 was paid by the victim to the police and he was subsequently released,” Maluleke said in a statement. He said the matter was later reported to the Hawks for investigation. “After conducting a successful investigation, the first accused was arrested at his workplace and was released on R2 000 bail after making his first appearance in the Sekhukhune Magistrates Court on 9 December 2021,” Maluleke said. The second accused was sought by police until he was arrested and brought before the Sekhukhune Magistrates Court on Wednesday, 1 June. “He was joined by his co-accused and was granted R2 000 bail. The case was postponed to 7 July for both accused,” Maluleke added.